CommonFields.Title: Dynamic mechanical analysis of polyvinylalcohol/silica nanocomposite
Author: Peng, Zheng
Kong, Ling Xue
Li, Si Dong
CommonFields.Location: Centre for Advanced Manufacturing Research, University of South Australia, Mawson Lakes SA 5095, Australia

PROCESSING.ExperimentalProcedure:
The PVA/SiO2 nanocomposite was prepared using self
    assembly monolayer technique

Mixing.Description:
Positively charged polyallylamine hydrochloride (PAH)
          molecular chains are absorbed on the surface of negatively charged
          SiO2 nanocomposites through electrostatic absorptive
          interaction.

PVA molecular chains are then assembled onto the
          surface of SiO2 nanoparticles through hydrogen bonding interaction
          between the hydroxy groups of PVA and the amino groups of
          PAH.

Nanoparticles are dispersed in PVA matrix
          uniformly.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description:
Dynamic and quasi-thermal mechanical analysis was performed
      on the same instrument.
